{"questionId": "acd30391", "correctAnswer": "D", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Extract the interior condition from standard form", "content": "The equation $(x+3)^2 + (y-1)^2 = 25$ reveals center $(-3, 1)$ and radius $5$. A point lies in the interior if and only if $(x+3)^2 + (y-1)^2 < 25$."}, {"title": "Test each choice by substitution", "content": "<ul><li>A $(-7,3)$: $(-7+3)^2 + (3-1)^2 = (-4)^2 + 2^2 = 16 + 4 = 20 < 25$ ✓ Interior</li><li>B $(-3,1)$: $(-3+3)^2 + (1-1)^2 = 0^2 + 0^2 = 0 < 25$ ✓ Interior</li><li>C $(0,0)$: $(0+3)^2 + (0-1)^2 = 3^2 + (-1)^2 = 9 + 1 = 10 < 25$ ✓ Interior</li><li>D $(3,2)$: $(3+3)^2 + (2-1)^2 = 6^2 + 1^2 = 36 + 1 = 37 > 25$ ✗ Outside</li></ul>The value for choice D is $37$, which exceeds $25$, placing $(3,2)$ outside the circle. That matches choice D — <strong>D</strong> is correct."}]}